user.description:
K L E F (DEEMED TO BE UNIVERSITY)
Center for INNOVATION, INCUBATION & ENTREPRENEURSHIP & KL Technology Incubators Foundation
KLEF (Deemed to be University) being a pioneering institute supporting Academics and Research in Engineering, Science & Technology, Architecture and Management is endowed with the infrastructure and highly experienced faculty and has succeeded in establishing Entrepreneurship Development Cell (EDC) in 2013 and later was converted to Center for Innovation, Incubation and Entrepreneurship (CIIE) with its vision: To foster innovation driven entrepreneurship through incubation, in alignment with KL University vision to become global University and promoting Technopreneurship, Women Entrepreneurship, Rural Entrepreneurship, Social Entrepreneurship & IP Cell.
Till date CIIE with 750 registered student members has organized and hosted more than 60 events on entrepreneurship varying from Hackathons, Ideation programs, Boot camps, Domain specific seminars including TEDxKLU talks by leading Personalities. Visits were made to Incubation Centers of APIS of AP & THub of Telangana. University has been recognized to act as Venture Development Center (VDC) certified by International Institute of Entrepreneurship Development (i2E) initiated by APSSDC, Government of AP in association with North Eastern University of Boston, USA.
CIIE has also conducted a Two day mega start up event "Start Up Rendezvous" that includes ideation camps, seminars, panel discussions & Start Up expo. Some of the admired events organized by CIIE are Entrepreneurship Awareness & Idea Generation programmes, GOOGLE Start up Event, STARTAP Fest, Startup weekend in Association with NASSCOM, Idea Generation Campaigns, Smart India Hackathon, Climathon, Design Competition.
University has been recognized as Nodal center to host Grand Finale of Smart India Hackathon 2017. KLU's Center for Innovation, Incubation, and Entrepreneurship (CIIE) was extended the National Business and Service Excellence Award 2016 by Praxis Media in association with Business Synergy. Mr. A Gopi Raja of EEE 3rd year student has won best idea presentation award during August Fest event held at Hyderabad in 2016 and he established a Venture "Fopple Drones Technologies Pvt., Ltd.," for manufacturing Drones for Agriculture. Mr. Surya Vamsi & Saketh Reddy of SuBrains has got State level third prize in Smart Idea Pitch & Win Contest conducted by APSSDC of Government of AP & NE University, Boston, USA. Six teams of university has participated in the Grand Finale of Smart India Hackathon 2017 & 2018
3 Start Up ventures out of 45 have been given an initial seed fund of Rs. 5,00,000/- per each Start Up and few more ventures are ready to get funding from the center. The university's Board of Management (BoM) has approved a budget of Rs. 50,00,000 towards seed funding for each of the financial years 2016-2017, 2017-2018 & 2018-2019 to incubate start-ups submitted by University's students and stake holders including faculty and staff & from surrounding area of capital region of Andhra Pradesh.
Till date 45 start Ups have been registered as incubatee under CIIE of KLUniversity varying from Technology to E-commerce platforms. The names of the Start-Ups initiated by the students of University for the last three years are TECHSTARTINC, FOPPLE, REPAIRKAREGA, FIPPLE, ISTHRIWALA, SUBRAINS, POROUS ASPHALT PAVEMENTS, FORMER PRICE, E-FORKS, PRINTSKOOL.COM, DESIGN AREANA, PRAAN RAKSHAK, KLUfn, i-Solutions, FOODPINE, PLANTSSHIP, SMARTGREEN, KL Radio.
Four virtual Start ups have been registered as Incubatees with CIIE. Some of the graduated incubatees from University till date are Plantsship, Isthriwala, Printskool, HouseDekho, "Broom Pick Solutions", "Fest Samachar", "Misplaced Minds", "Jago". CIIE is operating a separate cell in the name of "IP Cell" to provide IP related services to all the incubatee start ups.
KL's Center for Innovation Incubation and Entrepreneurship is operating with a separate entity "KL Technology Incubators Foundation" to look after and encourage startup ecosystem in the university campus and also provide opportunity to local aspiring entrepreneurs

user.description:
The Assam Agricultural University is proud to announce the establishment of an Incubation Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship in the Jorhat and Guwahati campus. This incubator aims to serve the entire North East Region and has therefore, aptly been positioned as “North East Agriculture Technology entrepreneurs Hub (NEATeHub)”. The incubator has been recognised as an “Atal Incubation Centre” by NITI Aayog, Government of India and as a “Knowledge Partner under the RKVY-RAFTAAR scheme” by the Department of Agri Cooperation & Farmers Welfare, Govt. of India.


The NEATeHUB has been set up to create a robust and sustainable entrepreneurial ecosystem/ support infrastructure to build successful startups in the area of agri and allied agriculture. The Incubator has elements such as physical space and infrastructure, common service delivery systems, network activities, partnerships and linkages – both institutional and individual, mentors and advisors – to enable startups to structure their business and make them “investment-ready” to potential investors. And finally, the incubator helps the startup figure out when it is time to leave and fly out of the incubator.


The NEATeHub aims to serve startups that are at any of the three developmental stages – (i) Idea stage, (ii) Product stage, (iii) Established stage but needs acceleration. The core areas of focus at the incubator are agri technologies across Horticulture/ Food science, Tea-based/plantation products, Organic inputs/ plant production products, Animal husbandry and dairy products, Non-food/ community science, Other niche, mushroom / value-added products, Farm services – advisory, mechanisation, CHC, market & weather intelligence, etc.

user.name: CSIR-IIIM- Technology Business Incubator
user.description:
The concept of Technology Business Incubator (TBI) has emerged at CSIR-Indian Institute of Integrative Medicine (IIIM), Jammu as a novel and a very pro-active approach. IIIM-TBI is an organizational setup that nurtures ideas, juvenile technologies of the companies by hand holding them survive during the start-up period. IIIM-TBI supports entrepreneurs, new start ups, researchers, students, institutes / universities,scientists, small or medium companies who plan to incubate their ideas or budding technologies into commercially successful ventures.



The main objective of the IIIM-TBI is to produce successful business ventures that create jobs and wealth in the J&K region, along with encouraging an attitude of innovation in the country as a whole



IIIM-TBI is a Section 8 company incorporated on 23 Feb 2017 and is supported by Department of Science and Technology. The thrust area of IIIM Incubator is development of Phytopharmaceutical and Nutraceutical  Products. The objective of the company is to nurture novel ideas, juvenile technologies of the knowledge driven companies and promote/carry out research for discovering herbal cures for unmet disease areas for Indian population. It also focuses on promoting skill development and entrepreneurship in the area of botanical/herbal drugs/nutraceutical products/phytopharmaceuticals by acting as a Technology Business Incubator and providing incubation ecosystem to entrepreneurs/ SMEs.

 

TBI enables all SMEs and start-ups with access to specialized equipment's, technology transfer and intellectually property management services; access to the state-of-art library resources; business assistance;networking support for marketing of finished products; manpower training and capacity building. At IIIM-TBI, we provide overall support, mentorship and handholding to start-up entrepreneurs during the complete product developmentcycle.

 

At IIIM-TBI, we have best in-class scientific intellectual andinfrastructural support in five potential areas:



1. WHO standard cGMP pilot plant facility.

2. State of the art Industrial Scale Fermentation facility.

3. NABL accredited Quality control (QC) and Quality Assurance (QA).

4. GLP standard in vivo laboratory; World class animal house for drug testing.

5. Kilo lab and scale-up facility for complex chemistry.


Apart from incubation support, we also provide manpower/entrepreneurship training to graduates from various universities or colleges from across the country.
